-- Nissan says August China auto sales up one percent
-- 
-- Tue Sep 3, 2013 3:01am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/09/03/us-nissan-china-idUSBRE98206Q20130903

 

 SHANGHAI  (Reuters) - Nissan Motor Co Ltd ( 7201.T ) and its local joint-venture sold 86,000 automobiles in China in August, up 1 percent from a year earlier, the Japanese automaker said on Tuesday. 
 That follows a 1.8 percent year-on-year rise in July and a 7.7 percent decline in June. In the first eight months of this year, Nissan sold a total of 768,500 vehicles, down 6.3 percent from a year earlier. Nissan makes vehicles in China in partnership with Dongfeng Automobile Group Co ( 0489.HK ). (Reporting by Samuel Shen and Kazunori Takada)